item.description:

Ian Levitt then continues with Robert Baril for the rest of the program.

item.title: The Daily Report Hour 1 - August 13, 2014
item.dc:creator: AM950productionasst
item.description:
Host Ian Levitt is joined in-studio by Nancy Nelson and Steve Bucher for the first segment to discuss the Minnesota primaries.

Ari Berman then joins the show to talk about the history of voting rights in the United States.  Ari is a contributing writer to the Nation Magazine.

Local comedian and host of “Laughing Matters”, Robert Baril, stops in to take a lighter look at local, national and international news and politics.
